This is about running a script of type: string, without using the program editor.

Since the machine doesn't handle substrings in any way other than as a list, we'll have to create a database that centralizes all the strings used by the system (In progress).

This will allow us to run a configuration, similar to ASM on the homescreen, or in a elaborate 'Prgm' configuration:

In the following way:

expr("STRING").

As a bonus, this is what will allow us to generate code !
By reversing the writing, that is by putting functions like "setMode(" → string and system strings → variables, in our case it will be a DATABASE.
